As discussed earlier, I am emailing regarding Sheila.F bed 43.

I have completed a transfers Ax with Sheila; I have also observed on couple of occasions how the carers are transferring her from bed to chair and chair to bed.
I have identified she requires a stand hoist/aid+ maximum AO2. One person has to support Sheila to sit at the edge of the bed, help her to shuffle to the edge of the bed, she doesn’t put any effort to weight bear or maintain sitting, this can be variable due to her dementia. I had a conversation with the daughter along with Kerry stretch (Senior carer), daughter was constantly saying that she has seen her mum walk with the zimmer frame at hospital with the physios, she has made her mum walk to the toilet at willow court, maybe they were able to do it but I have to recommend a more sustainable, consistent and safe transfers method that is using the stand hoist/aid.
I did explain this to the daughter, but she declined saying she doesn’t have room for equipment, and she also reported to Kerry S that she doesn’t want carers at home.
Daughter also mentioned that at hospital they said that Sheila can be discharged home and be at her upstairs bedroom, but if there is any necessity the family will carry her down the stairs, I found this very concerning and inappropriate.

Please speak to the family and let me know so that we can start the next steps as she requires specialist equipment it will take more 2 weeks for it to be delivered from the date of order.
